summary: The document is a confidential inquiry about the declassification status and accessibility of certain documents pertaining to Jean Rene Soute, alias Michel Roux, an OAS Captain. These documents, which include FBI and CIA reports, are thought to be connected to the JFK assassination investigation and are likely housed in the National Archives in College Park, Maryland. The inquiry specifies particular record and file numbers for the documents in question and hints at the possibility that some details about these documents may have been shared online.
key_findings: Inquiry seeks confirmation on the declassification and accessibility of documents linked to Jean Rene Soute/Michel Roux.
Documents encompass FBI and CIA reports, potentially associated with the JFK assassination probe.
Specific record and file numbers for the documents are provided.
Indicates that some information about these documents might have been disseminated on the Internet.
